==English==
===Verb===
'''polished off'''  (Past tense)


#Removed by [[polishing]] (rubbing with a fine abrasive).
#:''White rice is rice that has had the brownish hull '''polished off''' leaving just the white inner part of the grain.''
#Finished, done.  (As i the final step, polishing is done.  Especially said of eating.)
#:''We '''polished off''' the last of the work and went home early.''
#:''He '''polished off''' the last of the spaghetti in record time, he must have been very hungry.''